# Major Research Lessons

## Lesson 1

> **USDCHF may not generate many volatility-expansion opportunities, but when those opportunities occur they appear to be of higher quality than the more frequent opportunities found on GBPUSD.**

### Evidence

| Asset | Signals | Best Result |
|---------|---------:|----------:|
| GBPUSD BB Alone | 4,675 | 52.90% |
| USDCHF BB Alone | 1,248 | 53.75% |

This mirrors the RSI chapter almost perfectly.

---

## Lesson 2

> **The market matters more than the indicator.**

The same asset that produced one of the strongest RSI results also produced the strongest BB Alone result among the forex pairs tested.

The indicator changed.

The market personality did not.

---

## Lesson 3

> **Extremely selective filters can create statistically impressive results that may have little practical value due to opportunity scarcity.**

### Evidence

#### BB + Inside Bar

```text
65.15%
66 signals
```

#### BB + Doji

```text
68.00%
25 signals
```

As selectivity increased:

```text
Signals ↓
Win Rate ↑
```

But opportunity frequency collapsed.

---

## Lesson 4

> **A filter should be judged not only by how much it improves win rate, but also by how many opportunities it destroys.**

USDCHF provided some of the strongest examples of this lesson in the entire project.

---

## Lesson 5

> **Win rate alone is not enough. An edge should be evaluated by both its accuracy and its payoff.**

Several BB studies produced respectable win rates while generating weak or inconsistent average returns.

