# Chapter Verdict

The strongest conclusion from the USDCHF Bollinger Band chapter is:

> **Volatility expansion contains some predictive information on USDCHF, but RSI remains the stronger, more scalable, and more robust measure of mean reversion.**

While Inside Bars and Dojis produced impressive headline statistics, those results came from extremely small samples and should be treated cautiously.

The chapter ultimately reinforces one of the most important findings of the entire project:

> **The market matters more than the indicator.**

USDCHF behaved like USDCHF regardless of whether the market was being measured through momentum (RSI) or volatility (Bollinger Bands).

